<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
		Intentionally NOT sandboxed.

		The app ships with Developer ID + hardened runtime (notarized) and is
		distributed via DMG/GitHub, not the Mac App Store, so the sandbox is
		optional. Sandboxing broke Sparkle auto-updates: a sandboxed app can't
		reach Sparkle's installer XPC services (SPM doesn't name them per-app, so
		the -spk* mach lookup returns "No such process") and can't obtain the
		installer authorization right, so updates failed with "Update error!".
		Without the sandbox, Sparkle's standard installer works.

		Hardened runtime stays enabled via the ENABLE_HARDENED_RUNTIME build
		setting (required for notarization); no app entitlements are needed.
	-->
</dict>
</plist>
